Acting President David Mabuza has declared a Special Provincial Official Funeral Category 2 for late struggle stalwart and freedom fighter Dr Thandi Cynthia Ndlovu. The Acting President issued the declaration on Wednesday in honour of Ndlovu’s role and loyal service to the people of South Africa. A Special Official Provincial Funeral Category 2 entails elements of police ceremonial honours in line with The Presidency’s State, Official and Provincial Official Funeral Policy for distinguished persons, specifically designated by the President of the Republic of South Africa. Ndlovu lost her life on Saturday in a car accident in Rustenburg in the North West province. “The Acting President has once again, on behalf of government and the people of South Africa, conveyed his condolences to the Ndlovu family, friends, business associates and her comrades for this sad loss,” said the Presidency. The Acting President of the Republic of South Africa has ordered that The National Flag be flown at half-mast at all flag stations in the Gauteng Province on the day of the funeral. Details of the funeral service for the late Ndlovu will be communicated by the Gauteng Provincial Government. – SAnews.gov.za